01:00.522 --> 01:02.055
Who's that?

01:02.057 --> 01:03.322
Horace Guilder.

01:03.324 --> 01:06.359
Deputy director, Department of Defense.

01:06.361 --> 01:07.794
You had a rough week, Mark.

01:07.796 --> 01:09.596
What the hell's going on around here?

01:09.598 --> 01:11.665
We're in uncharted territory.

01:14.402 --> 01:16.670
We need to make this thing work.

01:16.672 --> 01:18.805
We're a billion dollars in.

01:18.807 --> 01:21.741
I need some kind of positive result.

01:21.743 --> 01:23.376
Understood.

01:23.378 --> 01:25.714
He created several very expensive

01:25.717 --> 01:27.894
tactical technology programs.

01:27.897 --> 01:31.350
He's famous for taking
credit and avoiding blame.

01:31.352 --> 01:34.687
My bet is that he's here because
of what happened to Paulson.

01:34.689 --> 01:36.889
I don't like it.

01:36.891 --> 01:38.557
You want me to keep going?

01:38.559 --> 01:39.825
No.

01:39.827 --> 01:41.894
I just like to know the score.

01:41.896 --> 01:44.063
We have that in common.

01:53.474 --> 01:56.675
How do you feel about getting
the hell out of this place?

01:56.677 --> 01:58.243
You got a plan?

01:58.245 --> 01:59.917
I know you have a relationship

01:59.920 --> 02:01.619
with him, but why is Brad Wolgast

02:01.622 --> 02:03.353
running around like
he's back on the team?

02:03.356 --> 02:04.655
The consensus was that

02:04.658 --> 02:06.216
it made the little
girl more comfortable.

02:06.218 --> 02:08.286
What's her name again?
Amy.

02:08.288 --> 02:09.854
Amy.

02:09.856 --> 02:11.623
When we were up in that tree house,

02:11.625 --> 02:13.758
I saw that there's a door
outside the mess hall.

02:13.760 --> 02:16.128
The cooks prop it open to smoke.

02:16.130 --> 02:17.940
Smoking is gross.

02:17.943 --> 02:19.397
It is. Never do it.

02:19.399 --> 02:23.074
So they probably disabled
the alarm on that door,

02:23.077 --> 02:25.337
which means...
We use it to sneak out.

02:25.339 --> 02:27.539
Then what? We're just standing outside.

02:28.775 --> 02:31.176
Use that brain.

02:31.178 --> 02:33.978
The slimy old pipe on
the edge of the lawn?

02:33.980 --> 02:35.880
It's not slimy, and it's not a pipe.

02:35.882 --> 02:37.428
It's a drainage tunnel.

02:37.431 --> 02:39.431
It's probably been out
of service for years.

02:39.434 --> 02:41.519
It'll take us out of here.
What about spiders?

02:41.521 --> 02:42.787
There are no spiders.

02:42.789 --> 02:44.055
Brown widows.

02:44.057 --> 02:46.157
You're thinking about them right now.

02:46.159 --> 02:48.092
The webs getting in your mouth

02:48.094 --> 02:49.560
and your face while you're crawling

02:49.562 --> 02:52.096
through that slimy tunnel.
Okay, stop.

02:53.298 --> 02:55.532
You in or out?

02:55.535 --> 02:57.635
I'm in.

02:57.637 --> 03:00.157
I need to meet with Amy alone.

03:00.160 --> 03:02.439
Get Wolgast away from her.

03:07.480 --> 03:11.149
Can I say again that I think
what you're doing is insane?

03:11.151 --> 03:14.185
I was exposed to Carter's blood.

03:14.187 --> 03:17.154
So if I turn...
You're not gonna turn.

03:17.156 --> 03:19.455
The safest place for me is 4B.

03:19.458 --> 03:22.559
I'm not gonna be responsible
for another person's death.

03:22.561 --> 03:24.061
Plus...

03:24.063 --> 03:26.663
takes me out of commission
while Guilder's here.

03:27.800 --> 03:30.266
I'd rather be down with the vampires.

03:30.268 --> 03:32.169
We don't say "vampire."

03:32.171 --> 03:33.770
Whatever.

03:37.176 --> 03:39.509
What are you gonna tell Guilder?

03:39.511 --> 03:41.678
The truth.

03:41.680 --> 03:44.181
We used science we didn't understand

03:44.183 --> 03:46.650
to create a lethal
species with superpowers

03:46.653 --> 03:49.886
that we can't control, who
seem hell-bent on destroying us.

03:49.888 --> 03:51.554
Oops.

03:52.825 --> 03:54.224
Yeah.
Mm.

03:54.226 --> 03:56.526
Let me know how that goes.

03:58.062 --> 04:00.430
Listen.

04:00.432 --> 04:01.764
If I turn...

04:01.767 --> 04:03.766
You're not gonna turn.

04:03.768 --> 04:05.341
If I turn...

04:05.344 --> 04:06.802
I got you.

04:08.406 --> 04:09.606
One shot.

04:09.608 --> 04:12.275
Right there. I'll do it myself.

04:12.277 --> 04:14.344
Don't wait.

04:17.382 --> 04:19.180
You're ready for quarantine.

04:20.779 --> 04:24.881
There's someone I need
to see before I go.

